\par A }{\b\f0 func_rotrain}{\f0  combines the features of func_train and func_rotating entities. A func_rotrain uses path_corners in the same way as a func_train does, with added information stored in the path_corners to control rotation. To
 establish the point about which rotation occurs, an origin brush should be included as part of the func_rotrain.
\par 
\par There are several behaviors that can be applied to func_rotrains. These are applied }{\i\f0 per path_corner}{\f0 . }{\i\f0 Translation}{\f0  refers to the movement between path_corners.
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1.\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls1\adjustright {\f0 Translate w/no rotation.
